Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Friday and welcome back to our 58th Weekly Dose of Optimism.
In Tuesday=E2=80=99s essay [ https://substack.com/redirect/563ce211-ae8c-4d=
b2-96c1-1f7491a9d6df?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa=
8-6m8ExkRNpU ], Packy addressed the popular complaint that, because we no l=
onger construct cathedrals, humans just don=E2=80=99t know how to build bea=
utiful things anymore. On cue, we=E2=80=99re leading off this week=E2=80=99=
s Weekly Dose of Optimism with four stories on the beautiful things we huma=
ns can build.
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.
The Weekly Dose is brought to you by=E2=80=A6 Write of Passage [ https://su=
bstack.com/redirect/e86d487c-e55e-4b1a-8057-7be511d78058?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3=
QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
We can=E2=80=99t recommend Write of Passage [ https://substack.com/redirect=
/e86d487c-e55e-4b1a-8057-7be511d78058?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlN=
uaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] highly enough, but we=E2=80=99ll try.=20
WoP is the writing course that Packy took back in 2019 that jumpstarted his=
 writing career. The course is run by David Perrell, and it was started wit=
h the simple belief that when you publish your ideas online, you unleash th=
e full power of the Internet. For Packy, it worked: he went from no audienc=
e in 2019 to over 200K subscribers and a full-time career in internet writi=
ng just a couple of years later.
Write of Passage [ https://substack.com/redirect/e86d487c-e55e-4b1a-8057-7b=
e511d78058?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRN=
pU ] is a five-week online experience, where you will learn to grow a meani=
ngful, profitable presence on the Internet. Completing the course is an inv=
estment of both time and money, but for thousands of folks like Packy, it=
=E2=80=99s been the best professional decision they=E2=80=99ve ever made.
The next cohort of Write of Passage [ https://substack.com/redirect/e86d487=
c-e55e-4b1a-8057-7be511d78058?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlX=
XepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] starts later this fall and open-enrollment starts S=
eptember 12th. But prior to that, Write of Passage is offering a free works=
hop with Cultural Tutor [ https://substack.com/redirect/af1bdc68-bcd4-4701-=
ac52-b71e3d9e722f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU ]. In the workshop, you=E2=80=99ll learn how he went from working=
 at McDonalds to 1.5M Twitter followers all by writing online. Grow Your Au=
dience with the Cultural Tutor [ https://substack.com/redirect/e86d487c-e55=
e-4b1a-8057-7be511d78058?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKb=
qOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] in on Wednesday September 6th, but you can register now =
[ https://substack.com/redirect/e86d487c-e55e-4b1a-8057-7be511d78058?j=3Dey=
J1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. It=E2=80=99=
s a great way to sample the Write of Passage experience, prior to committin=
g.
(1) Wind power with a=C2=A0high-tech twist could help ships burn less=C2=A0=
fuel [ https://substack.com/redirect/f4c444c2-7136-4cb9-a713-0c48b999dcb6?j=
=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Maria Gallucci [ https://substack.com/redirect/e360e0a6-034b-43fd-8aea-287d=
dcf8f401?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU=
 ] for Canary Media=20
The Pyxis Ocean, a=C2=A0750-foot-long bulk carrier, is the first vessel to =
deploy WindWings [ https://substack.com/redirect/62cd4d78-9b34-4c44-9661-b1=
89055e6fe6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRN=
pU ], which can stand up to 123=C2=A0feet tall and are made from the same d=
urable material as wind turbines. The prototype devices could potentially c=
urb the ship=E2=80=99s diesel fuel consumption =E2=80=94 and its resulting =
greenhouse gas emissions =E2=80=94 by roughly one-fifth.
Not only are we capable of building beautiful things today, they also tend =
to be more functional. Take the newly retrofired Pyxis Ocean, a bulk carrie=
r equipped with sail-like wind turbines that could reduce the ship=E2=80=99=
s greenhouse gas emissions by ~20%.
The maritime industry accounts for nearly 3% global CO2 emissions. And as w=
e all experienced during the supply chain crisis, it=E2=80=99s also critica=
l for maintaining our way of life. The solution to the industry=E2=80=99s e=
missions problem is not to stop shipping things, or even to ship less thing=
s. That would be disastrous. One solution is to use technology, like these =
=E2=80=9Cwind-wings,=E2=80=9D to reduce the emissions per shipment.
We=E2=80=99re still early here =E2=80=94 there=E2=80=99s approximately 50,0=
00-60,000 cargo ships in the world and only one is currently outfitted with=
 this technology. But proving out feasibility is important. Over time, more=
 ships will be outfitted, we=E2=80=99ll develop new technologies that make =
the wind-wings more efficient, and then eventually, a whole new technology =
will drop that lowers emissions so much that the wind-wings will be obsolet=
e.
We still know how to build beautiful, functional things.=20
(Ed. Note: Just getting in a =E2=80=9CA sailboat. You invented a sailboat.=
=E2=80=9D before the comments.)
(2) Building homes in a FACTORY | Cover [ https://substack.com/redirect/a7d=
ea2b2-a7fe-4d5e-9c4a-58c986b71755?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZ=
jmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Speaking of building beautiful, functional things=E2=80=A6
The US is currently suffering a shortage of 5 million homes, and 90% of bui=
lding projects end up over-budget or delayed. Most homes are still built on=
-site, piece by piece with stick-framing, hammers, and nails=E2=80=94as the=
y have been for the last century. It=E2=80=99s an incredibly fragmented and=
 inefficient building process.
Cover is flipping that process on its head, in an effort to solve the US=E2=
=80=99 housing shortage. The company uses software to design custom homes a=
nd then produces those homes right in its LA factory. The result is beautif=
ully designed, affordable custom homes. Pre-fab has been tried (and failed)=
 before, but Cover is taking a fresh approach that learns from those pitfal=
ls, as seen in the video and as founder Alexis Rivas discussed on Invest Li=
ke the Best [ https://substack.com/redirect/b8907a18-bb47-4050-8edb-ac583b7=
c5526?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] =
in April.=20
Our man Jason Carman [ https://substack.com/redirect/c283683f-67de-4a86-895=
2-903f6c621e0c?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8E=
xkRNpU ], of Astranis and Saturday Startup Stories, covered everything you =
need to know about Cover in this YouTube video [ https://substack.com/redir=
ect/a7dea2b2-a7fe-4d5e-9c4a-58c986b71755?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_=
ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. We=E2=80=99re a big fan of Jason=E2=80=
=99s work=E2=80=A6he=E2=80=99s dropping high-quality videos weekly on the t=
ypes of companies we write about at Not Boring =E2=80=94 ambitious companie=
s, building beautiful things to solve real world challenges. And he turns t=
hem around in like a day.=20
(3) Champion-level drone racing using deep reinforcement learning [ https:/=
/substack.com/redirect/0b4e3d62-9b2e-4aa4-9708-3011308d6548?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXA=
wZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Kaufmann et al for Nature
The "Swift" AI drone combines deep reinforcement learning in simulation wit=
h data collected in the physical world. This marks the first time that an a=
utonomous mobile robot has beaten human champions in a real physical sport =
designed for and by humans. The key difference to previous achievements, li=
ke IBM=E2=80=99s Deep Blue winning against Gary Kasparov at chess in 1996 o=
r Google DeepMind=E2=80=99s AlphaGo crushing the top champion Lee Sedol at =
Go in 2016, is that the previous feats were limited to board games or video=
 games.
OK, IDK if I agree with the paper=E2=80=99s assertion that drone racing is =
a =E2=80=9Creal physical sport.=E2=80=9D Honestly, if drone racing is a spo=
rt then I=E2=80=99m also calling myself an athlete for publishing this news=
letter every week. But whether it=E2=80=99s a sport or not is kind of besid=
es the point. The important thing to note is that we now have AI-powered dr=
ones capable of outperforming human drivers.
As noted, that=E2=80=99s a big deal for this =E2=80=9Csport=E2=80=9D, but t=
he implications spread well beyond a couple of hobbyist-athletes racing dro=
nes for kicks. A company like Anduril could use high-performance AI-powered=
 drones to keep soldiers safe on the battlefield or Amazon could use them t=
o increase the feasibility of drone delivery.
Whether drone racing is a sport or not, it holds true that what starts out =
looking like a toy can often end up being the next big thing.
(4) Behind the Scenes of a Nuclear Microreactor Startup w/ Matt Loszak, Fou=
nder CEO of Aalo Atomics [ https://substack.com/redirect/2fac2085-e4fd-4965=
-be45-9f3effa69fc9?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-=
6m8ExkRNpU ]
Eric Jorgenson [ https://substack.com/redirect/b056fed2-1cbc-4097-84a7-17a5=
8b25a55a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU=
 ] for Smart Friends
This conversation is an in-depth primer on the history of nuclear energy in=
 America and an analysis of where things are headed, with a nuclear energy =
practitioner. Matt Loszak [ https://substack.com/redirect/7d9e9109-2b20-43d=
e-8409-81d3be74cef7?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8=
-6m8ExkRNpU ] is the founder and CEO of Aalo Atomics [ https://substack.com=
/redirect/c38d860f-5de7-4311-a865-d8de9094d3f6?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5=
T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], a startup whose mission is to mak=
e nuclear microreactors that could achieve 3=C2=A2/kWh electricity.
Putting aside the ambition of the project for a second, Matt is a good exam=
ple of a new breed of founder that=E2=80=99s become more common over the la=
st couple of years. He touches on his journey in the pod, but a quick glanc=
e at his LinkedIn [ https://substack.com/redirect/4363721a-4a12-43fb-ae61-9=
56a7ffd1887?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU ] reveals that he successfully started two previous companies =E2=80=94=
 a social media app and an SMB HR/payroll platform =E2=80=94 and has now tu=
rned his attention and talents towards tackling a problem as impactful and =
complex as nuclear microreactors. Good Quests [ https://substack.com/redire=
ct/e015a48b-281d-4bb5-bb5b-9a121302022f?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_Z=
lNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] ftw.
If this keeps up, who knows, maybe one day we might be able to turn in thes=
e 140 characters for nuclear-powered flying cars.
(5) The Cynical Genius Illusion: Exploring and Debunking Lay Beliefs About =
Cynicism and Competence [ https://substack.com/redirect/7e40b980-5c4d-4316-=
86f3-15d5e509897d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6=
m8ExkRNpU ]
h/t Ethan Mollick [ https://substack.com/redirect/5c86d503-dc22-4e48-b825-1=
1660821f086?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkR=
NpU ]
Four studies showed that laypeople tend to believe in cynical individuals=
=E2=80=99 cognitive superiority. A further three studies based on the data =
of about 200,000 individuals from 30 countries debunked these lay beliefs a=
s illusionary by revealing that cynical (vs. less cynical) individuals gene=
rally do worse on cognitive ability and academic competency tasks.
And oldie, but a goodie re-emerged on X this week [ https://substack.com/re=
direct/5c86d503-dc22-4e48-b825-11660821f086?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7G=
nA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. The the main findings of the study, =
which was based on a survey of 200,000 individuals, are:
People think that cynical people are smarter than other people
Cynical people are less smart than less cynical people
Less competent people embrace cynicism as a protective strategy
Taken together, it goes something like this: We think cynical people are sm=
art, but they are not any smarter than less cynical people; in fact, less s=
mart people adopt cynicism as a defense mechanism.=20
So if you encounter any unnecessary cynicism this weekend, just know where =
it=E2=80=99s coming from.
That=E2=80=99s all for this week. Packy is taking the week off for Labor Da=
y, so no Tuesday essay this week, but we=E2=80=99ll be back in your inbox F=
riday.
Thanks for reading,
Dan + Packy

